article.headline: UC Riverside 76, Cal Poly-SLO 69
article.story: SAN LUIS OBISPO, Calif. -- Rudy Meo and Konner Veteto each scored 13 points in leading UC Riverside to a 76-69 win over Cal Poly Saturday. With the win UC Riverside improved to 17-12 (8-8, Big West Conference) and earned the sixth seed for the Big West Conference Tournament. They'll face seventh seed Cal State Fullerton on Wednesday in the first round of play at the tournament. The Mustangs conclude the 2008-09 season with a 7-21 overall record and a 3-13 mark in conference play. Cal Poly sophomore Shawn Lewis led all scorers with 23 points while junior Lorenzo Keeler and Justin Brown added 12 and 13 points respectively.
